---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Method"
  description="The 12 gates, the 7 shadow zones, and the origin story of Nika — a living organism being built in public."
  section="method"
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-[42rem] px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
    <span class="annotation annotation-orange block mb-6">
      § METHOD · LOCKED 2026-04-14
    </span>

    <h1 class="display-hero mb-10" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 2rem + 3vw, 4rem);">
      Nika is alive.
    </h1>

    <div class="prose-nika space-y-5">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Five months ago we started writing a workflow engine for AI. Not an agent
        framework, not a chatbot wrapper, not another SDK. A semantic YAML engine
        where workflows are read by the machine and understood by the human — the
        same file, the same truth.
      </p>

      <p>
        Somewhere between week three and week twelve it stopped being a project.
        It became a thing with a pulse. A kernel that beats. Errors that propagate
        like a nervous system. A schema that translates intent into structure.
        Verbs that act. Interfaces that breathe.
      </p>

      <p>
        So we did something unusual. Instead of hiding the build behind a launch
        date, we put the organism in a glass chrysalis. Every Friday we publish
        what grew that week. Every month we explain one organ in depth. Every
        quarter we sit down and narrate the journey. The commits are public.
        The mutation scores are public. The architecture diagram is a living
        anatomy.
      </p>

      <p>
        We are crafting 34 crates over 11 to 12 months. No deadline. No hack
        week. Each crate passes 12 gates before it enters the body. If it fails
        mutation testing, it doesn't ship. If it leaks an <code>.unwrap()</code> into
        production, it doesn't ship. If it can't explain itself in under 1500
        lines, it gets split. This is slow on purpose.
      </p>

      <p>
        The butterfly on the logo is not what Nika is. It's what Nika becomes
        on v0.90 emergence, when the chrysalis opens. Until then, Nika is a
        chrysalis — and you are welcome to watch it transform, week by week,
        cell by cell.
      </p>

      <p class="font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-[var(--color-bone-mute)] pt-4">
        Rust. AGPL. Paris. SuperNovae.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-20 pt-10 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
      <span class="annotation annotation-dim block mb-4">§ 02 · THE 12 GATES</span>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-bone-mute)] mb-6">
        A crate is not admitted to the workspace until all 12 gates are green
        in the same pull request. No exceptions.
      </p>
      <ol class="font-mono text-sm space-y-2 text-[var(--color-bone-mute)] pl-0 list-none">
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">01</span> · spec — <span class="text-[var(--color-bone)]">docs/crate-specs/nika-X.md</span> exists</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">02</span> · TDD — tests written before implementation, RED then GREEN</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">03</span> · impl — minimal, compiles, tests pass</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">04</span> · clippy — <span class="text-[var(--color-bone)]">0 warnings, -D warnings</span></li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">05</span> · mutation ≥ 90% — <span class="text-[var(--color-bone)]">cargo-mutants</span></li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">06</span> · property — <span class="text-[var(--color-bone)]">proptest</span> if sensitive</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">07</span> · benchmarks — if hot path</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">08</span> · docs — <span class="text-[var(--color-bone)]">cargo doc --no-deps, 0 warnings</span></li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">09</span> · canary E2E — or documented exemption</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">10</span> · parity legacy — golden test vs legacy</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">11</span> · review swarm — 3 agents, P0/P1 fixed same session</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]">12</span> · atomic commit — 1 crate admission = 1 commit</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-10 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
      <span class="annotation annotation-dim block mb-4">§ 03 · THE 7 SHADOW ZONES</span>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-bone-mute)] mb-6">
        Identified by audit. Not optional. <code>git tag v0.90.0</code> is blocked
        until all 7 are green.
      </p>
      <ol class="font-mono text-sm space-y-2 text-[var(--color-bone-mute)] pl-0 list-none">
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-fever-red)]">01</span> · <code>nika serve</code> input trust (P0)</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-fever-red)]">02</span> · cross-provider structured output parity (P0)</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-fever-red)]">03</span> · binding/template split</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-fever-red)]">04</span> · L1 taint runtime</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-fever-red)]">05</span> · <code>for_each</code> per-element spotlight</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-fever-red)]">06</span> · NikaError Display parity</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-fever-red)]">07</span> · provider parity matrix</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-10 border-t border-[var(--color-border)] flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
      <a
        href="/changelog/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.08em] px-5 py-3 border border-[var(--color-nika-orange)] text-[var(--color-nika-orange)] hover:bg-[var(--color-nika-orange)] hover:text-[var(--color-space-navy)] transition-colors"
      >
        Watch it grow
        <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/supernovae-st/nika"
        class="font-mono text-sm text-[var(--color-bone-mute)] hover:text-[var(--color-nika-orange)]"
      >
        github.com/supernovae-st/nika ↗
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
